                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13734855" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2013 14:48:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You basically can never set listen_address to an unspecified IP address, because gossip needs a way to communicate with the node.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13734868" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2013 15:01:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t we make it reject invalid addresses instead of starting up and NPEing later?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13735214" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 9 Aug 2013 20:05:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can do that, though the only invalid IP is 0.0.0.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13736211" author="dbrosius" created="Sun, 11 Aug 2013 06:32:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;255.&lt;b&gt;.&lt;/b&gt;.* and multicast addresses are bad as well, altho probably unlikely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13766815" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 13 Sep 2013 19:02:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trivial patch to throw when listen_address is 0.0.0.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776304" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 13:37:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any reason not to check the cases Dave mentioned?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776381" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 15:16:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are just too many possibilities, if someone screws up their subnetting.  192.168.0.255 would be invalid in a /24 due to being the broadcast address, but so would 192.168.0.3 in a /30.  255.* is just a special case of this problem.  I don&apos;t think anyone is really going to do this, or use multicast, so it doesn&apos;t seem worth bothering with.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777105" author="dbrosius" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 03:20:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13777593" author="brandon.williams" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2013 15:10:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
